1SG Snow;

This is the imagery, from Google Earth, regarding the Holston Army
Ammunition Plant (HAAP).

I am not an imagery analyst. You may be, but I certainly am not.

Please take a look at the imagery, identify potential NAIs based on what we
know of the scenario. Hopefully, the OPORD will be published sooner
rather than later... at least ours will.

We will have foot patrols and sUAS platforms for "aerial surveillance." Of
course, we WILL NOT be taking imagery or video of anything within the
perimeter fence line of the installation. The main point of using sUAS
platforms during the exercise is to test the installation drone detection
system. Therefore, imagery / video taking is a moot point.

We can discuss this via telephone should you want to give me a call at your
convenience.

I would like us to develop a situational brief to include the weather
considerations, the critical points that you see on the installation, and
the respective NAIs. We can discuss further.

-- 
V/R

JOHN T. SHEAF
LTC, TNSG
